The paper focuses on understanding the collaborative dynamics of software projects by investigating the roles of developers. This falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also uses network analysis to model the organizational structure, which is related to social networks (cs.SI) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper examines the validity of operationalizations based on developer activities, which is related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
